step.info:
figcaption{
 color:blue;
}You can also use DITA style CSS classes to achieve the same
          effect:*[class ~= "topic/fig"] >*[class ~= "topic/title"] {
 color:blue;
}

As you can see, the caption is split into multiple span elements, each with a class.
          This makes it easy to style them separately. You can start by hiding the current "."
          separator:.fig--title-label-punctuation {
  display:none;
}and use the figure number as an anchor to add a new synthetic element that
          will contain the new separator
          ":".fig--title-label-number:after{
  content:": ";
}
